{"name": "realerikrani-flaskapierr", "metadata": {"name": "realerikrani-flaskapierr", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["werkzeug"], "summary": "Error handling models and functions for Flask-based APIs", "upload_time": 1734685342}, "documentation": ["# flaskapierr\n\nRegister the error handler\n\n```py\nfrom flask import Flask\nfrom realerikrani.flaskapierr import handle_error\n\n# ...\n\ndef create() -> Flask:\n    app = Flask(\"api\")\n    app.register_blueprint(todo_blueprint, url_prefix=\"/todos\")\n    app.register_error_handler(Exception, handle_error)\n    return app\n```\n\n... and use the error classes for raising errors from Flask blueprints.\n\n```py\nfrom realerikrani.flaskapierr import Error, ErrorGroup\n\n# ...\n\n@todo_blueprint.route(\"\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef create_todo():\n    try:\n        todo = repo.create_todo(dict(request.json))\n    except TodoAlreadyExistsError as ve:\n        raise ErrorGroup(\"409\", [Error(ve.message, ve.code)]) from None\n\n    return {\"todo\": asdict(todo)}, 201\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "realerikrani.flaskapierr", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.Error", "xref": {"fqname": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.error.Error", "project": null}}, {"name": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.ErrorGroup", "xref": {"fqname": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.error.ErrorGroup", "project": null}}, {"name": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.handle_error", "xref": {"fqname": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.error_handler.handle_error", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.error", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.error.Error", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "realerikrani.flaskapierr.error.Error.message", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "pro